data.enText: a tall plant grown for its large yellow grains that are used for making flour or eaten as a vegetable; the grains of this plant

tr: tall annual cereal grass bearing kernels on large ears: widely cultivated in America in many varieties
the principal cereal in Mexico and Central and South America since pre-Columbian times

value.def: Maize is a tall plant which produces long objects covered with yellow seeds called sweetcorn. It is often grown as a food crop.
